You are working on Spotify Radar — a Node.js/Express app deployed on Railway with a Supabase (PostgreSQL) database.

Rules:
- Never remove the 350 review cap (MAX_REVIEWS_FOR_ANALYSIS). It controls Claude API costs.
- Never modify the keyword filter without updating the keyword count in the UI.
- Never log or store raw review text with user PII — reviews are public data only.
- Always keep the competitor-only exclusion filter in keywordFilter.js.
- Do not add new npm packages without checking Railway compatibility first.
- Do not change the Claude model from claude-sonnet-4-6 without explicit instruction.
- The Bluesky 100% relevance rate is a known architectural limitation — do not file it as a bug.
- Keep stripDashes() applied to all AI-rendered text fields.
- All new scraper sources must go through the keyword filter before being stored.
- Do not expose the Supabase connection string or Claude API key in any frontend file.